{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"At the break, I was asked by several people"},{"time":2000,"text":"about my comments about the aging debate."},{"time":5000,"text":"And this will be my only comment on it."},{"time":7000,"text":"And that is, I understand"},{"time":9000,"text":"that optimists greatly outlive pessimists."},{"time":11000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":16000,"text":"What I'm going to tell you about in my 18 minutes is"},{"time":19000,"text":"how we're about to switch from reading the genetic code"},{"time":23000,"text":"to the first stages of beginning"},{"time":25000,"text":"to write the code ourselves."},{"time":28000,"text":"It's only 10 years ago this month"},{"time":30000,"text":"when we published the first sequence"},{"time":32000,"text":"of a free-living organism,"},{"time":34000,"text":"that of haemophilus influenzae."},{"time":36000,"text":"That took a genome project"},{"time":38000,"text":"from 13 years down to four months."},{"time":42000,"text":"We can now do that same genome project"},{"time":44000,"text":"in the order of"},{"time":46000,"text":"two to eight hours."},{"time":48000,"text":"So in the last decade, a large number of genomes have been added:"},{"time":51000,"text":"most human pathogens,"},{"time":54000,"text":"a couple of plants,"},{"time":56000,"text":"several insects and several mammals,"},{"time":59000,"text":"including the human genome."},{"time":62000,"text":"Genomics at this stage of the thinking"},{"time":65000,"text":"from a little over 10 years ago"},{"time":67000,"text":"was, by the end of this year, we might have"},{"time":69000,"text":"between three and five genomes sequenced;"},{"time":72000,"text":"it's on the order of several hundred."},{"time":75000,"text":"We just got a grant from the Gordon and Betty Moore Foundation"},{"time":78000,"text":"to sequence 130 genomes this year,"},{"time":81000,"text":"as a side project from environmental organisms."},{"time":85000,"text":"So the rate of reading the genetic code has changed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":89000,"text":"But as we look, what's out there,"},{"time":91000,"text":"we've barely scratched the surface"},{"time":93000,"text":"on what is available on this planet."},{"time":97000,"text":"Most people don't realize it, because they're invisible,"},{"time":100000,"text":"but microbes make up about a half of the Earth's biomass,"},{"time":104000,"text":"whereas all animals only make up about"},{"time":107000,"text":"one one-thousandth of all the biomass."},{"time":109000,"text":"And maybe it's something that people in Oxford don't do very often,"},{"time":112000,"text":"but if you ever make it to the sea,"},{"time":114000,"text":"and you swallow a mouthful of seawater,"},{"time":117000,"text":"keep in mind that each milliliter"},{"time":119000,"text":"has about a million bacteria"},{"time":121000,"text":"and on the order of 10 million viruses."}]},{"cues":[{"time":124000,"text":"Less than 5,000 microbial species"},{"time":127000,"text":"have been characterized as of two years ago,"},{"time":129000,"text":"and so we decided to do something about it."},{"time":131000,"text":"And we started the Sorcerer II Expedition,"},{"time":134000,"text":"where we were, as with great oceanographic expeditions,"},{"time":137000,"text":"trying to sample the ocean every 200 miles."},{"time":142000,"text":"We started in Bermuda for our test project,"},{"time":144000,"text":"then moved up to Halifax,"},{"time":146000,"text":"working down the U.S. East Coast,"},{"time":148000,"text":"the Caribbean Sea, the Panama Canal,"},{"time":153000,"text":"through to the Galapagos, then across the Pacific,"},{"time":155000,"text":"and we're in the process now of working our way"},{"time":157000,"text":"across the Indian Ocean."},{"time":159000,"text":"It's very tough duty; we're doing this on a sailing vessel,"},{"time":162000,"text":"in part to help excite young people"},{"time":164000,"text":"about going into science."},{"time":167000,"text":"The experiments are incredibly simple."},{"time":169000,"text":"We just take seawater and we filter it,"},{"time":172000,"text":"and we collect different size organisms on different filters,"},{"time":176000,"text":"and then take their DNA back to our lab in Rockville,"},{"time":179000,"text":"where we can sequence a hundred million letters"},{"time":182000,"text":"of the genetic code every 24 hours."},{"time":184000,"text":"And with doing this,"},{"time":186000,"text":"we've made some amazing discoveries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":188000,"text":"For example, it was thought that the visual pigments"},{"time":190000,"text":"that are in our eyes -- there was only one or two organisms"},{"time":193000,"text":"in the environment that had these same pigments."},{"time":197000,"text":"It turns out, almost every species"},{"time":199000,"text":"in the upper parts of the ocean"},{"time":201000,"text":"in warm parts of the world"},{"time":203000,"text":"have these same photoreceptors,"},{"time":205000,"text":"and use sunlight as the source of their energy"},{"time":208000,"text":"and communication."},{"time":210000,"text":"From one site, from one barrel of seawater,"},{"time":213000,"text":"we discovered 1.3 million new genes"},{"time":216000,"text":"and as many as 50,000 new species."}]},{"cues":[{"time":220000,"text":"We've extended this to the air"},{"time":222000,"text":"now with a grant from the Sloan Foundation."},{"time":225000,"text":"We're measuring how many viruses and bacteria"},{"time":227000,"text":"all of us are breathing in and out every day,"},{"time":230000,"text":"particularly on airplanes"},{"time":232000,"text":"or closed auditoriums."},{"time":234000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":237000,"text":"We filter through some simple apparatuses;"},{"time":239000,"text":"we collect on the order of a billion microbes from just a day"},{"time":242000,"text":"filtering on top of a building in New York City."},{"time":246000,"text":"And we're in the process of sequencing all that"},{"time":248000,"text":"at the present time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":250000,"text":"Just on the data collection side,"},{"time":252000,"text":"just where we are through the Galapagos,"},{"time":255000,"text":"we're finding that almost every 200 miles,"},{"time":257000,"text":"we see tremendous diversity"},{"time":259000,"text":"in the samples in the ocean."},{"time":262000,"text":"Some of these make logical sense,"},{"time":264000,"text":"in terms of different temperature gradients."},{"time":267000,"text":"So this is a satellite photograph"},{"time":269000,"text":"based on temperatures -- red being warm,"},{"time":271000,"text":"blue being cold --"},{"time":274000,"text":"and we found there's a tremendous difference between"},{"time":277000,"text":"the warm water samples and the cold water samples,"},{"time":279000,"text":"in terms of abundant species."},{"time":282000,"text":"The other thing that surprised us quite a bit"},{"time":284000,"text":"is these photoreceptors detect different wavelengths of light,"},{"time":288000,"text":"and we can predict that based on their amino acid sequence."},{"time":292000,"text":"And these vary tremendously from region to region."},{"time":295000,"text":"Maybe not surprisingly,"},{"time":297000,"text":"in the deep ocean, where it's mostly blue,"},{"time":299000,"text":"the photoreceptors tend to see blue light."},{"time":303000,"text":"When there's a lot of chlorophyll around,"},{"time":305000,"text":"they see a lot of green light."},{"time":307000,"text":"But they vary even more,"},{"time":309000,"text":"possibly moving towards infrared and ultraviolet"},{"time":312000,"text":"in the extremes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":315000,"text":"Just to try and get an assessment"},{"time":317000,"text":"of what our gene repertoire was,"},{"time":319000,"text":"we assembled all the data --"},{"time":321000,"text":"including all of ours thus far from the expedition,"},{"time":324000,"text":"which represents more than half of all the gene data on the planet --"},{"time":327000,"text":"and it totaled around 29 million genes."},{"time":331000,"text":"And we tried to put these into gene families"},{"time":333000,"text":"to see what these discoveries are:"},{"time":335000,"text":"Are we just discovering new members of known families,"},{"time":338000,"text":"or are we discovering new families?"},{"time":340000,"text":"And it turns out we have about 50,000"},{"time":342000,"text":"major gene families,"},{"time":345000,"text":"but every new sample we take in the environment"},{"time":348000,"text":"adds in a linear fashion to these new families."},{"time":351000,"text":"So we're at the earliest stages of discovery"},{"time":353000,"text":"about basic genes,"},{"time":356000,"text":"components and life on this planet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":360000,"text":"When we look at the so-called evolutionary tree,"},{"time":363000,"text":"we're up on the upper right-hand corner with the animals."},{"time":367000,"text":"Of those roughly 29 million genes,"},{"time":371000,"text":"we only have around 24,000"},{"time":373000,"text":"in our genome."},{"time":375000,"text":"And if you take all animals together,"},{"time":377000,"text":"we probably share less than 30,000"},{"time":380000,"text":"and probably maybe a dozen"},{"time":383000,"text":"or more thousand different gene families."},{"time":387000,"text":"I view that these genes are now"},{"time":389000,"text":"not only the design components of evolution."},{"time":392000,"text":"And we think in a gene-centric view --"},{"time":394000,"text":"maybe going back to Richard Dawkins' ideas --"},{"time":397000,"text":"than in a genome-centric view,"},{"time":399000,"text":"which are different constructs of these gene components."}]},{"cues":[{"time":404000,"text":"Synthetic DNA, the ability to synthesize DNA,"},{"time":407000,"text":"has changed at sort of the same pace"},{"time":409000,"text":"that DNA sequencing has"},{"time":411000,"text":"over the last decade or two,"},{"time":413000,"text":"and is getting very rapid and very cheap."},{"time":416000,"text":"Our first thought about synthetic genomics came"},{"time":418000,"text":"when we sequenced the second genome back in 1995,"},{"time":422000,"text":"and that from mycoplasma genitalium."},{"time":424000,"text":"And we have really nice T-shirts that say,"},{"time":427000,"text":"you know, \"I heart my genitalium.\""},{"time":429000,"text":"This is actually just a microorganism."},{"time":433000,"text":"But it has roughly 500 genes."},{"time":437000,"text":"Haemophilus had 1,800 genes."},{"time":439000,"text":"And we simply asked the question,"},{"time":441000,"text":"if one species needs 800, another 500,"},{"time":443000,"text":"is there a smaller set of genes"},{"time":445000,"text":"that might comprise a minimal operating system?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":449000,"text":"So we started doing transposon mutagenesis."},{"time":452000,"text":"Transposons are just small pieces of DNA"},{"time":455000,"text":"that randomly insert in the genetic code."},{"time":457000,"text":"And if they insert in the middle of the gene, they disrupt its function."},{"time":461000,"text":"So we made a map of all the genes"},{"time":463000,"text":"that could take transposon insertions"},{"time":465000,"text":"and we called those \"non-essential genes.\""},{"time":468000,"text":"But it turns out the environment is very critical for this,"},{"time":471000,"text":"and you can only"},{"time":473000,"text":"define an essential or non-essential gene"},{"time":476000,"text":"based on exactly what's in the environment."},{"time":480000,"text":"We also tried to take a more directly intellectual approach"},{"time":482000,"text":"with the genomes of 13 related organisms,"},{"time":487000,"text":"and we tried to compare all of those, to see what they had in common."},{"time":491000,"text":"And we got these overlapping circles. And we found only 173 genes"},{"time":495000,"text":"common to all 13 organisms."},{"time":498000,"text":"The pool expanded a little bit if we ignored"},{"time":500000,"text":"one intracellular parasite;"},{"time":502000,"text":"it expanded even more"},{"time":504000,"text":"when we looked at core sets of genes"},{"time":506000,"text":"of around 310 or so."},{"time":508000,"text":"So we think that we can expand"},{"time":510000,"text":"or contract genomes, depending on your point of view here,"},{"time":513000,"text":"to maybe 300 to 400 genes"},{"time":516000,"text":"from the minimal of 500."}]},{"cues":[{"time":518000,"text":"The only way to prove these ideas"},{"time":521000,"text":"was to construct an artificial chromosome with those genes in them,"},{"time":524000,"text":"and we had to do this in a cassette-based fashion."},{"time":527000,"text":"We found that synthesizing accurate DNA"},{"time":529000,"text":"in large pieces was extremely difficult."},{"time":532000,"text":"Ham Smith and Clyde Hutchison, my colleagues on this,"},{"time":535000,"text":"developed an exciting new method"},{"time":537000,"text":"that allowed us to synthesize a 5,000-base pair virus"},{"time":540000,"text":"in only a two-week period"},{"time":542000,"text":"that was 100 percent accurate,"},{"time":545000,"text":"in terms of its sequence and its biology."},{"time":548000,"text":"It was a quite exciting experiment -- when we just took the synthetic piece of DNA,"},{"time":552000,"text":"injected it in the bacteria and all of a sudden,"},{"time":554000,"text":"that DNA started driving the production of the virus particles"},{"time":559000,"text":"that turned around and then killed the bacteria."},{"time":562000,"text":"This was not the first synthetic virus --"},{"time":564000,"text":"a polio virus had been made a year before --"},{"time":568000,"text":"but it was only one ten-thousandth as active"},{"time":570000,"text":"and it took three years to do."},{"time":573000,"text":"This is a cartoon of the structure of phi X 174."},{"time":577000,"text":"This is a case where the software now builds its own hardware,"},{"time":581000,"text":"and that's the notions that we have with biology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":585000,"text":"People immediately jump to concerns about biological warfare,"},{"time":589000,"text":"and I had recent testimony before a Senate committee,"},{"time":593000,"text":"and a special committee the U.S. government has set up"},{"time":595000,"text":"to review this area."},{"time":597000,"text":"And I think it's important to keep reality in mind,"},{"time":600000,"text":"versus what happens with people's imaginations."},{"time":604000,"text":"Basically, any virus that's been sequenced today --"},{"time":607000,"text":"that genome can be made."},{"time":609000,"text":"And people immediately freak out about things about Ebola or smallpox,"},{"time":613000,"text":"but the DNA from this organism is not infective."},{"time":617000,"text":"So even if somebody made the smallpox genome,"},{"time":620000,"text":"that DNA itself would not cause infections."},{"time":624000,"text":"The real concern that security departments have"},{"time":627000,"text":"is designer viruses."},{"time":629000,"text":"And there's only two countries, the U.S. and the former Soviet Union,"},{"time":633000,"text":"that had major efforts"},{"time":635000,"text":"on trying to create biological warfare agents."},{"time":638000,"text":"If that research is truly discontinued,"},{"time":641000,"text":"there should be very little activity"},{"time":643000,"text":"on the know-how to make designer viruses in the future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":647000,"text":"I think single-cell organisms are possible within two years."},{"time":651000,"text":"And possibly eukaryotic cells,"},{"time":654000,"text":"those that we have,"},{"time":656000,"text":"are possible within a decade."},{"time":659000,"text":"So we're now making several dozen different constructs,"},{"time":663000,"text":"because we can vary the cassettes and the genes"},{"time":666000,"text":"that go into this artificial chromosome."},{"time":668000,"text":"The key is, how do you put all of the others?"},{"time":670000,"text":"We start with these fragments,"},{"time":672000,"text":"and then we have a homologous recombination system"},{"time":675000,"text":"that reassembles those into a chromosome."}]},{"cues":[{"time":679000,"text":"This is derived from an organism, deinococcus radiodurans,"},{"time":682000,"text":"that can take three million rads of radiation and not be killed."},{"time":688000,"text":"It reassembles its genome after this radiation burst"},{"time":692000,"text":"in about 12 to 24 hours,"},{"time":694000,"text":"after its chromosomes are literally blown apart."},{"time":697000,"text":"This organism is ubiquitous on the planet,"},{"time":699000,"text":"and exists perhaps now"},{"time":701000,"text":"in outer space due to all our travel there."},{"time":705000,"text":"This is a glass beaker after"},{"time":707000,"text":"about half a million rads of radiation."},{"time":709000,"text":"The glass started to burn and crack,"},{"time":711000,"text":"while the microbes sitting in the bottom"},{"time":713000,"text":"just got happier and happier."},{"time":715000,"text":"Here's an actual picture of what happens:"},{"time":717000,"text":"the top of this shows the genome"},{"time":719000,"text":"after 1.7 million rads of radiation."},{"time":722000,"text":"The chromosome is literally blown apart."},{"time":724000,"text":"And here's that same DNA automatically reassembled"},{"time":728000,"text":"24 hours later."},{"time":730000,"text":"It's truly stunning that these organisms can do that,"},{"time":733000,"text":"and we probably have thousands,"},{"time":735000,"text":"if not tens of thousands, of different species"},{"time":737000,"text":"on this planet that are capable of doing that."},{"time":740000,"text":"After these genomes are synthesized,"},{"time":742000,"text":"the first step is just transplanting them"},{"time":744000,"text":"into a cell without a genome."}]},{"cues":[{"time":748000,"text":"So we think synthetic cells are going to have tremendous potential,"},{"time":752000,"text":"not only for understanding the basis of biology"},{"time":755000,"text":"but for hopefully environmental and society issues."},{"time":758000,"text":"For example, from the third organism we sequenced,"},{"time":761000,"text":"Methanococcus jannaschii -- it lives in boiling water temperatures;"},{"time":765000,"text":"its energy source is hydrogen"},{"time":767000,"text":"and all its carbon comes from CO2 it captures back from the environment."},{"time":772000,"text":"So we know lots of different pathways,"},{"time":774000,"text":"thousands of different organisms now"},{"time":777000,"text":"that live off of CO2,"},{"time":779000,"text":"and can capture that back."},{"time":781000,"text":"So instead of using carbon from oil"},{"time":784000,"text":"for synthetic processes,"},{"time":786000,"text":"we have the chance of using carbon"},{"time":789000,"text":"and capturing it back from the atmosphere,"},{"time":792000,"text":"converting that into biopolymers"},{"time":794000,"text":"or other products."},{"time":796000,"text":"We have one organism that lives off of carbon monoxide,"},{"time":799000,"text":"and we use as a reducing power"},{"time":801000,"text":"to split water to produce hydrogen and oxygen."},{"time":805000,"text":"Also, there's numerous pathways"},{"time":807000,"text":"that can be engineered metabolizing methane."},{"time":811000,"text":"And DuPont has a major program with Statoil in Norway"},{"time":815000,"text":"to capture and convert the methane"},{"time":817000,"text":"from the gas fields there into useful products."}]},{"cues":[{"time":821000,"text":"Within a short while, I think there's going to be a new field"},{"time":823000,"text":"called \"Combinatorial Genomics,\""},{"time":825000,"text":"because with these new synthesis capabilities,"},{"time":828000,"text":"these vast gene array repertoires"},{"time":831000,"text":"and the homologous recombination,"},{"time":833000,"text":"we think we can design a robot to make"},{"time":835000,"text":"maybe a million different chromosomes a day."},{"time":839000,"text":"And therefore, as with all biology,"},{"time":841000,"text":"you get selection through screening,"},{"time":844000,"text":"whether you're screening for hydrogen production,"},{"time":846000,"text":"or chemical production, or just viability."},{"time":849000,"text":"To understand the role of these genes"},{"time":851000,"text":"is going to be well within reach."}]},{"cues":[{"time":853000,"text":"We're trying to modify photosynthesis"},{"time":856000,"text":"to produce hydrogen directly from sunlight."},{"time":859000,"text":"Photosynthesis is modulated by oxygen,"},{"time":862000,"text":"and we have an oxygen-insensitive hydrogenase"},{"time":865000,"text":"that we think will totally change this process."},{"time":870000,"text":"We're also combining cellulases,"},{"time":872000,"text":"the enzymes that break down complex sugars into simple sugars"},{"time":875000,"text":"and fermentation in the same cell"},{"time":878000,"text":"for producing ethanol."},{"time":881000,"text":"Pharmaceutical production is already under way"},{"time":883000,"text":"in major laboratories"},{"time":885000,"text":"using microbes."},{"time":887000,"text":"The chemistry from compounds in the environment"},{"time":890000,"text":"is orders of magnitude more complex"},{"time":892000,"text":"than our best chemists can produce."},{"time":895000,"text":"I think future engineered species"},{"time":897000,"text":"could be the source of food,"},{"time":899000,"text":"hopefully a source of energy,"},{"time":901000,"text":"environmental remediation"},{"time":904000,"text":"and perhaps"},{"time":906000,"text":"replacing the petrochemical industry."}]},{"cues":[{"time":908000,"text":"Let me just close with ethical and policy studies."},{"time":912000,"text":"We delayed the start of our experiments in 1999"},{"time":916000,"text":"until we completed a year-and-a-half bioethical review"},{"time":919000,"text":"as to whether we should try and make an artificial species."},{"time":923000,"text":"Every major religion participated in this."},{"time":926000,"text":"It was actually a very strange study,"},{"time":928000,"text":"because the various religious leaders were using their scriptures as law books,"},{"time":933000,"text":"and they couldn't find anything in them prohibiting making life,"},{"time":936000,"text":"so it must be OK. The only ultimate concerns"},{"time":939000,"text":"were biological warfare aspects of this,"},{"time":943000,"text":"but gave us the go ahead to start these experiments"},{"time":946000,"text":"for the reasons we were doing them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":948000,"text":"Right now the Sloan Foundation has just funded"},{"time":950000,"text":"a multi-institutional study on this,"},{"time":953000,"text":"to work out what the risk and benefits to society are,"},{"time":956000,"text":"and the rules that scientific teams such as my own"},{"time":959000,"text":"should be using in this area,"},{"time":961000,"text":"and we're trying to set good examples as we go forward."},{"time":965000,"text":"These are complex issues."},{"time":967000,"text":"Except for the threat of bio-terrorism,"},{"time":969000,"text":"they're very simple issues in terms of,"},{"time":971000,"text":"can we design things to produce clean energy,"},{"time":975000,"text":"perhaps revolutionizing"},{"time":977000,"text":"what developing countries can do"},{"time":980000,"text":"and provide through various simple processes."},{"time":983000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]}]}